            "heading": "Why Celebs Love “Sabya” aka Sabyasachi Sarees",
            "text": "<p>If you scroll through red-carpet looks, celebrity weddings, or fashion weeks, it’s hard to miss the iconic drapes from Sabyasachi. From Bollywood brides to international events, his sarees seem to consistently be the go-to.</p><h2>Built on heritage + craftsmanship</h2><p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sabyasachi_Mukherjee\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Sabyasachi Mukherjee has built his brand on traditional textiles</span></a>, hand craftsmanship, hand-dye techniques, and artisanal weaving. He works with Indian handloom weavers, revives heritage crafts, and uses rich fabrics and classic motifs.</p><p>Because of that, his sarees carry craftsmanship that looks authentic and luxurious – <a href=\"https://zeezest.com/style-beauty/a-night-to-remember-celebs-stun-in-all-black-at-sabyasachi-s-25th-anniversary-8442?utm_source=chatgpt.com\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">qualities appreciated by celebs</span></a> who want something beyond fast fashion.</p>",
