            "text_size": "40,15",
            "txt_align": "start",
            "sub_heading": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2><br/>Brand + Social Optics</h2><p>There is also a bit of fashion optics: celebs know that wearing a Sabyasachi saree will get attention, because the brand is associated with luxury, handcraft, celebrity approvals, and heritage design. It’s a way to reinforce their style credentials.</p><p>Plus, the designer has built a strong reputation – from humble beginnings to a global name, collaborating with craftsmen, promoting traditional techniques, etc. That adds authenticity and allure.</p><h2>Important Takeaways</h2><ul><li>Celebrities favor these sarees because they are <strong>handcrafted with traditional craftsmanship</strong>, giving an authentic luxury feel.<br/><br/></li><li>The designs are custom, rich in fabrics, details, precious embellishments, and storytelling, making them perfect for red carpet or bridal moments.<br/><br/></li><li>Wearing a Sabyasachi saree signals <strong>heritage + status + emotional resonance</strong> — ideal for weddings, special events, or public appearances.<br/><br/></li><li>For celebs, a saree from this designer is also about <strong>branding and optics</strong>: you showcase elegance, exclusivity, and craftsmanship.<br/><br/></li><li>For you (or your customers), such sarees can be positioned as aspirational pieces: not just garments, but heirlooms, statement pieces, and investment wardrobe staples.</li></ul>",
